1
00:00:00,959 --> 00:00:03,294
<i>We should name our group!</i>

2
00:00:03,378 --> 00:00:05,296
<i>- Mabel?</i>
<i>- It's Mabel.</i>

3
00:00:05,380 --> 00:00:09,676
[cheerful shouts and laughter]

4
00:00:10,885 --> 00:00:12,429
<i>Did you also get Louisa's text?</i>

5
00:00:12,512 --> 00:00:13,763
<i>She said she's really leaving.</i>

6
00:00:13,847 --> 00:00:16,016
<i>Wow! She still had time to joke around.</i>

7
00:00:16,099 --> 00:00:17,058
<i>She's so unfair!</i>

8
00:00:17,142 --> 00:00:18,476
- [thwacks]
- [grunts]

9
00:00:18,560 --> 00:00:20,437
<i>Your friend got into another fight again</i>

10
00:00:20,520 --> 00:00:21,938
<i>and got hit on the head with a rock!</i>

11
00:00:22,021 --> 00:00:23,690
<i>Help!</i>

12
00:00:23,773 --> 00:00:25,775
<i>Help me, please!</i> [sobs]

13
00:00:26,526 --> 00:00:27,736
<i>Let me go!</i>

14
00:00:27,819 --> 00:00:28,820
<i>Louisa?</i>

15
00:00:28,903 --> 00:00:30,655
<i>Help-- Help!</i>

16
00:00:30,739 --> 00:00:32,449
<i>- Louisa!</i>
<i>- Louisa!</i>

17
00:00:32,991 --> 00:00:34,325
<i>Louisa!</i>

18
00:00:34,409 --> 00:00:35,785
<i>No!</i>

19
00:00:35,869 --> 00:00:36,995
<i>Louisa!</i>

20
00:00:37,078 --> 00:00:38,455
[wails] <i>Louisa!</i>

21
00:00:38,538 --> 00:00:41,708
[crying] <i>Louisa!</i>

22
00:00:41,791 --> 00:00:44,169
<i>Don't let go! Don't let go!</i>

23
00:00:44,252 --> 00:00:48,423
- [heart beating rapidly]
- [somber music playing]

24
00:00:56,431 --> 00:00:57,682
[screams] <i>Louisa!</i>

25
00:00:57,766 --> 00:01:00,602
[wailing] <i>Louisa!</i>

26
00:01:00,685 --> 00:01:01,770
<i>Louisa!</i>

27
00:01:01,853 --> 00:01:04,481
[gasps, pants]

28
00:01:07,567 --> 00:01:14,657
[theme music playing]

29
00:02:24,602 --> 00:02:27,230
[Erica] There is no
cure for an illegal arrest.

30
00:02:27,939 --> 00:02:29,899
The waiver of Article 125

31
00:02:29,983 --> 00:02:33,611
only cures the period that you are
detained without a valid warrant.

32
00:02:33,695 --> 00:02:35,780
When you waive Article 125,

33
00:02:35,864 --> 00:02:39,409
you're basically
saying that if you're arrested,

34
00:02:39,492 --> 00:02:41,244
you waive your right

35
00:02:41,327 --> 00:02:43,329
to be released from jail within 36 hours

36
00:02:43,413 --> 00:02:45,456
while the prosecutor is still deciding.

37
00:02:45,915 --> 00:02:48,710
But nothing cures an illegal arrest.

38
00:02:48,793 --> 00:02:53,172
[man] Attorney, we don't need
you to lecture us about law.

39
00:02:53,673 --> 00:02:55,508
We are all lawmakers here.

40
00:02:57,093 --> 00:02:59,178
It was clearly stated in the resolution

41
00:02:59,262 --> 00:03:01,264
of the investigating prosecutor

42
00:03:01,347 --> 00:03:04,726
that it's impossible for
your client not to understand

43
00:03:05,268 --> 00:03:06,978
what they signed.

44
00:03:07,061 --> 00:03:10,189
They were guided
by their previous lawyers.

45
00:03:10,273 --> 00:03:11,900
But why should we place the burden

46
00:03:11,983 --> 00:03:15,320
of the interpretation of Article 125
on the accused

47
00:03:15,904 --> 00:03:18,156
when even those who went to law school,

48
00:03:18,239 --> 00:03:21,242
our lawyers, and law enforcers,

49
00:03:21,326 --> 00:03:23,995
still have trouble understanding it?

50
00:03:24,078 --> 00:03:26,706
Since this is
an inquiry in aid of legislation,

51
00:03:26,789 --> 00:03:30,251
I think the Congress should make
our laws more understandable.

52
00:03:30,335 --> 00:03:33,671
[tense music playing]

53
00:03:37,008 --> 00:03:38,593
[music becomes gentle]

54
00:03:38,676 --> 00:03:40,178
[student] Good morning, ma'am!

55
00:03:40,261 --> 00:03:41,471
Good morning!

56
00:03:41,554 --> 00:03:43,431
- [school bell rings]
- [Beth] Uh, Jenny!

57
00:03:43,514 --> 00:03:45,391
- Jenny, wait.
- Yes, ma'am?

58
00:03:45,475 --> 00:03:46,684
Come here.

59
00:03:47,227 --> 00:03:49,771
So, has your mother
allowed you to go to Baguio?

60
00:03:49,854 --> 00:03:52,357
Um, no, ma'am.

61
00:03:52,440 --> 00:03:53,942
She won't allow me.

62
00:03:54,025 --> 00:03:56,903
Oh no, you're
supposed to represent our school.

63
00:03:56,986 --> 00:03:58,780
Do you want me to talk to your mother?

64
00:03:58,863 --> 00:04:02,408
Maybe she just doesn't understand
what a great this opportunity is for you.

65
00:04:02,492 --> 00:04:04,244
Especially after college.

66
00:04:04,327 --> 00:04:07,288
Didn't you say
you wanted to be a journalist?

67
00:04:07,372 --> 00:04:10,500
No need, ma'am.
She might say something to you.

68
00:04:10,583 --> 00:04:12,168
Uh, why?

69
00:04:12,252 --> 00:04:13,711
What did she say?

70
00:04:13,795 --> 00:04:15,588
She said that before,

71
00:04:15,672 --> 00:04:18,508
you wanted to be a reporter too,

72
00:04:18,591 --> 00:04:21,552
but you just ended up becoming a teacher.

73
00:04:22,720 --> 00:04:24,347
Ma! Ma!

74
00:04:24,430 --> 00:04:26,266
Uh, okay. Let's talk again tomorrow.

75
00:04:26,349 --> 00:04:28,685
Oh, okay, ma'am. Thank you.

76
00:04:28,768 --> 00:04:31,354
[mellow music playing]

77
00:04:31,813 --> 00:04:33,147
What is it now?

78
00:04:33,231 --> 00:04:37,694
If this is about picking up your
Aunt Alice tomorrow, fine, you can come.

79
00:04:37,777 --> 00:04:38,820
No, Ma!

80
00:04:38,903 --> 00:04:40,989
- What?
- Aunt Mel has a scandal!

81
00:04:41,072 --> 00:04:42,532
Huh? Let me see.

82
00:04:45,868 --> 00:04:50,039
[upbeat music playing]

83
00:04:51,916 --> 00:04:52,917
[photographer] There.

84
00:04:55,628 --> 00:04:57,005
Okay, okay! Gorgeous! Gorgeous!

85
00:04:57,088 --> 00:04:58,631
- Make it fierce.
- Just a minute.

86
00:04:59,215 --> 00:05:00,758
[Mel] This doesn't look right.

87
00:05:01,926 --> 00:05:03,219
Good! Nice one.

88
00:05:03,303 --> 00:05:04,554
Okay, let's go!

89
00:05:10,018 --> 00:05:12,437
[upbeat music fades]

90
00:05:13,313 --> 00:05:14,480
Who died?

91
00:05:15,857 --> 00:05:16,733
Mel.

92
00:05:17,525 --> 00:05:18,860
You have to see this.

93
00:05:23,114 --> 00:05:27,452
[unsettling music playing]

94
00:05:34,876 --> 00:05:36,127
[woman 1] Can you even do that?

95
00:05:36,210 --> 00:05:37,962
[indistinct chatter]

96
00:05:38,046 --> 00:05:39,047
Hey!

97
00:05:39,589 --> 00:05:40,631
You find this funny?

98
00:05:41,632 --> 00:05:44,218
Will it still be funny
when you all lose your jobs tomorrow?

99
00:05:44,302 --> 00:05:47,764
[unsettling music continues]

100
00:05:49,098 --> 00:05:50,099
[huffs]

101
00:05:50,183 --> 00:05:53,394
- [waves crashing]
- [unsettling music fades]

102
00:05:54,771 --> 00:05:59,067
[airplane rumbles]

103
00:06:07,366 --> 00:06:08,576
Come on, dear.

104
00:06:08,659 --> 00:06:12,538
[light-hearted music playing]

105
00:06:19,295 --> 00:06:20,922
- Excuse me.
- Is she here yet?

106
00:06:21,005 --> 00:06:22,173
I don't think so.

107
00:06:23,299 --> 00:06:24,300
Do you see her, Ma?

108
00:06:24,383 --> 00:06:25,802
Not yet.

109
00:06:25,885 --> 00:06:26,928
Is she close, Ma?

110
00:06:27,011 --> 00:06:28,846
They said she's already landed.

111
00:06:34,727 --> 00:06:37,772
Is that my friend?!
Alice Quintano Miller?!

112
00:06:38,689 --> 00:06:40,650
- Oh my god!
- Oh my god!

113
00:06:40,733 --> 00:06:42,485
Come on! She's here!

114
00:06:42,568 --> 00:06:43,778
- Wait!
- Oh my gosh!

115
00:06:43,861 --> 00:06:45,905
- [squeals]
- Welcome back!

116
00:06:45,988 --> 00:06:48,616
[laughter]

117
00:06:49,408 --> 00:06:50,952
I'm so happy! Is this your son?

118
00:06:51,035 --> 00:06:52,203
- Yes!
- I'm Aunt Beth.

119
00:06:52,286 --> 00:06:53,579
- Say hi.
- Hi, Aunt Beth.

120
00:06:53,663 --> 00:06:55,998
Hi! You're so handsome!

121
00:06:56,082 --> 00:06:58,417
This is Chloe and Uncle Ryan.

122
00:06:58,501 --> 00:06:59,752
- Hello.
- Hi.

123
00:06:59,836 --> 00:07:03,840
[light-hearted music continues]

124
00:07:19,689 --> 00:07:20,606
[Alice] Let's go.

125
00:07:21,524 --> 00:07:23,943
So, this is it.

126
00:07:24,360 --> 00:07:25,695
This is the house.

127
00:07:25,778 --> 00:07:26,946
What do you think, baby?

128
00:07:27,029 --> 00:07:28,239
Mom…

129
00:07:28,322 --> 00:07:29,782
I'm sleepy.

130
00:07:29,866 --> 00:07:31,659
Aww. So adorable.

131
00:07:31,742 --> 00:07:33,327
[in baby voice] You're sleepy?

132
00:07:33,411 --> 00:07:34,412
Okay.

133
00:07:34,495 --> 00:07:36,247
- He needs sleep.
- Yeah, go ahead.

134
00:07:36,330 --> 00:07:37,582
You sleep here. Come.

135
00:07:37,665 --> 00:07:39,125
[light-hearted music continues]

136
00:07:39,208 --> 00:07:40,460
[car door opens]

137
00:07:40,543 --> 00:07:42,587
Just sleep here.
I'll leave it on for you, okay?

138
00:07:42,670 --> 00:07:43,838
Okay, Mom.

139
00:07:45,047 --> 00:07:46,007
Love you.

140
00:07:46,883 --> 00:07:50,011
You're probably still jet lagged.
Let's just do this tomorrow.

141
00:07:50,094 --> 00:07:52,638
Oh no, I'm fine. I promise.

142
00:07:56,184 --> 00:07:57,310
You know,

143
00:07:57,393 --> 00:07:59,770
we used to hang out at this
exact spot back in high school.

144
00:07:59,854 --> 00:08:02,523
The view from
the balcony was absolutely to die for.

145
00:08:02,607 --> 00:08:04,901
- [pensive music playing]
- [Louisa sighs]

146
00:08:05,401 --> 00:08:07,445
[Louisa] <i>I promise you this. One day,</i>

147
00:08:07,528 --> 00:08:08,821
<i>I'll make it big</i>

148
00:08:08,905 --> 00:08:11,491
<i>and get a house like this.</i>

149
00:08:11,574 --> 00:08:12,909
[giggles]

150
00:08:13,910 --> 00:08:15,036
[sighs loudly]

151
00:08:17,371 --> 00:08:18,414
[exhales heavily]

152
00:08:19,916 --> 00:08:21,375
<i>It's so beautiful.</i>

153
00:08:21,459 --> 00:08:24,337
<i>Like the whole</i>
<i>world's right in front of you.</i>

154
00:08:24,420 --> 00:08:28,508
[pensive music continues]

155
00:08:31,677 --> 00:08:33,179
<i>I'm going to miss this.</i>

156
00:08:37,558 --> 00:08:39,602
[sighing]

157
00:08:40,228 --> 00:08:41,479
<i>But why miss anything?</i>

158
00:08:41,562 --> 00:08:43,773
<i>We can always come back anytime.</i>

159
00:08:46,651 --> 00:08:48,444
[scoffs] <i>I don't know.</i>

160
00:08:49,070 --> 00:08:50,363
<i>I mean,</i>

161
00:08:50,988 --> 00:08:52,156
<i>in just a few months,</i>

162
00:08:52,240 --> 00:08:54,575
<i>the three of you will</i>
<i>be off to Manila for college,</i>

163
00:08:55,117 --> 00:08:57,411
<i>while Erica and I stay behind.</i>

164
00:08:59,664 --> 00:09:01,165
<i>We'll all go our separate ways.</i>

165
00:09:01,249 --> 00:09:03,334
[music fades]

166
00:09:04,877 --> 00:09:06,963
<i>Okay, enough drama for today!</i>

167
00:09:07,046 --> 00:09:08,673
<i>Let's just chill! </i>[chuckles]

168
00:09:08,756 --> 00:09:10,258
<i>We'll deal with it later.</i>

169
00:09:10,341 --> 00:09:13,553
<i>Can we promise to meet here every year?</i>

170
00:09:13,970 --> 00:09:16,055
<i>Oh no, I can't promise that.</i>

171
00:09:16,472 --> 00:09:18,849
<i>What if I'm already abroad by then,</i>

172
00:09:18,933 --> 00:09:21,435
<i>covering a major world event?</i>

173
00:09:22,186 --> 00:09:23,563
<i>Here we go again.</i>

174
00:09:23,646 --> 00:09:25,356
[young Louisa] <i>Your imagination is wild.</i>

175
00:09:25,439 --> 00:09:26,899
<i>Already crafting your success story?</i>

176
00:09:26,983 --> 00:09:28,192
<i>This early?</i>

177
00:09:28,276 --> 00:09:29,902
<i>- Of course!</i>
<i>- Classic you.</i>

178
00:09:29,986 --> 00:09:32,446
<i>What if we all lived under one roof?</i>

179
00:09:32,530 --> 00:09:33,990
[bright music playing]

180
00:09:34,073 --> 00:09:36,576
<i>You want a house like this, right, Louisa?</i>

181
00:09:36,659 --> 00:09:38,744
<i>Then let's have one</i>
<i>built for the five of us.</i>

182
00:09:38,828 --> 00:09:41,414
<i>Once we're working and earning enough,</i>

183
00:09:41,497 --> 00:09:43,332
<i>we can live together.</i>

184
00:09:45,585 --> 00:09:47,044
[chuckles] Did your mom tell you?

185
00:09:47,128 --> 00:09:48,379
Yes, Auntie.

186
00:09:48,713 --> 00:09:52,216
But these days,
everyone knows it as a haunted house.

187
00:09:52,300 --> 00:09:54,343
And a MO spot. Right here.

188
00:09:55,011 --> 00:09:56,137
"MO"?

189
00:09:56,679 --> 00:09:58,222
Make out. That's what she meant.

190
00:09:58,306 --> 00:10:00,224
You! How do you even know that?

191
00:10:00,308 --> 00:10:01,517
Exactly, sweetheart.

192
00:10:01,601 --> 00:10:03,477
We didn't raise you that way.

193
00:10:03,561 --> 00:10:06,814
How could I not know?
I always catch you two making out.

194
00:10:06,897 --> 00:10:08,316
Hey! Psst! Look at this kid--

195
00:10:08,399 --> 00:10:10,776
Watch your mouth.
Aunt Alice is right there.

196
00:10:10,860 --> 00:10:12,111
- [giggles]
- That's for adults only.

197
00:10:12,194 --> 00:10:14,280
[playful music playing]

198
00:10:14,363 --> 00:10:15,698
[Ryan] It's finally happened.

199
00:10:16,365 --> 00:10:17,325
[Beth chuckles]

200
00:10:19,493 --> 00:10:20,953
[Chloe giggles]

201
00:10:21,037 --> 00:10:22,747
[Beth] Your dad can be so embarrassing.

202
00:10:22,830 --> 00:10:24,498
- Oh my!
- It's not true.

203
00:10:24,582 --> 00:10:26,167
[all chuckling]

204
00:10:26,250 --> 00:10:27,668
That explains the belly.

205
00:10:27,752 --> 00:10:31,297
[pensive music playing]

206
00:10:36,844 --> 00:10:38,095
Thanks, Beth.

207
00:10:38,179 --> 00:10:42,058
For taking care of everything,
from the sale to the renovation.

208
00:10:42,141 --> 00:10:43,809
I wish I could've done more to help.

209
00:10:43,893 --> 00:10:44,685
[Beth] Don't be silly.

210
00:10:44,769 --> 00:10:46,270
I'm the one who's here.

211
00:10:46,354 --> 00:10:47,980
It makes sense
that I take care of everything.

212
00:10:48,064 --> 00:10:51,233
Mel's always busy in Manila anyway.

213
00:10:51,776 --> 00:10:54,528
And since
your Uncle Edward owns the house,

214
00:10:54,612 --> 00:10:57,907
the buying process
wasn't complicated at all.

215
00:10:58,699 --> 00:10:59,659
[sighs softly]

216
00:10:59,742 --> 00:11:00,743
Ryan.

217
00:11:00,826 --> 00:11:03,120
Thank you for all your help, too.

218
00:11:03,204 --> 00:11:05,289
You bet I'm helping.

219
00:11:05,373 --> 00:11:06,624
My wife would kill me.

220
00:11:06,707 --> 00:11:08,876
[Chloe chuckles]

221
00:11:08,959 --> 00:11:12,546
I still can't believe
you two ended up together.

222
00:11:12,630 --> 00:11:13,923
[Beth giggles] Right?

223
00:11:14,006 --> 00:11:17,718
Did you know? Your mom
turned your dad down over and over.

224
00:11:17,802 --> 00:11:18,844
- I told you.
- Whatever.

225
00:11:18,928 --> 00:11:21,055
Oh, she always brings that up.

226
00:11:21,138 --> 00:11:22,390
[Beth, Chloe chuckling]

227
00:11:22,473 --> 00:11:25,559
Oh my god, the MABELs are back!

228
00:11:25,643 --> 00:11:26,769
- [giggles]
- [Beth] Mel!

229
00:11:26,852 --> 00:11:28,479
- [Mel] Hi!
- Oh my gosh!

230
00:11:28,562 --> 00:11:30,481
Hi, girls!

231
00:11:30,564 --> 00:11:32,400
- Hello!
- Hi!

232
00:11:32,483 --> 00:11:35,277
Oh my gosh,
I can't believe we're really doing this!

233
00:11:35,361 --> 00:11:36,946
- Finally!
- [Alice] Well…

234
00:11:37,029 --> 00:11:39,990
This is what we were
talking about fourteen years ago.

235
00:11:40,074 --> 00:11:43,369
That's right.
And honestly, to tell you the truth,

236
00:11:43,452 --> 00:11:45,079
we didn't take you seriously back then.

237
00:11:45,162 --> 00:11:46,205
[gasps]

238
00:11:46,288 --> 00:11:47,915
- [laughs] True.
- Well…

239
00:11:47,998 --> 00:11:49,250
I mean, see?

240
00:11:49,333 --> 00:11:50,918
My persuasion powers worked in the end.

241
00:11:51,001 --> 00:11:52,420
- That's right.
- [Beth giggles]

242
00:11:52,503 --> 00:11:54,964
I'm so happy! Finally! [giggling]

243
00:11:55,047 --> 00:11:56,924
So how are you--

244
00:11:57,007 --> 00:11:59,635
- [light music playing]
- [Mel breathing nervously]

245
00:12:00,302 --> 00:12:01,679
Please don't kill me.

246
00:12:02,138 --> 00:12:04,640
My PR team advised me to do this.

247
00:12:04,723 --> 00:12:06,434
You know, because of the scandal.

248
00:12:06,517 --> 00:12:09,061
So… what scandal?

249
00:12:12,690 --> 00:12:15,901
[Mel] So, I really need
the positive spin right now.

250
00:12:18,571 --> 00:12:19,822
So.

251
00:12:19,905 --> 00:12:21,407
What do we need to do?

252
00:12:21,490 --> 00:12:22,450
Um.

253
00:12:22,533 --> 00:12:23,826
Hi, I'm Tim.

254
00:12:24,493 --> 00:12:25,744
- Hi.
- This is Tom.

255
00:12:25,828 --> 00:12:26,829
- Hello.
- This is Tom.

256
00:12:26,912 --> 00:12:27,788
Beth.

257
00:12:27,872 --> 00:12:30,958
[Tim] They'll be
filming you and the house.

258
00:12:31,041 --> 00:12:34,462
We just need you to talk about the house
and explain why it's being renovated.

259
00:12:36,547 --> 00:12:37,715
I'm not comfortable with any of this.

260
00:12:38,132 --> 00:12:39,758
What? No! No, Beth!

261
00:12:39,842 --> 00:12:41,927
Beth, please! Please.

262
00:12:42,011 --> 00:12:43,304
I really need this.

263
00:12:43,846 --> 00:12:45,639
I've become a laughingstock online.

264
00:12:45,723 --> 00:12:47,099
I just need a win.

265
00:12:47,183 --> 00:12:49,226
[light music continues]

266
00:12:49,310 --> 00:12:50,769
Do it, Mama.

267
00:12:54,648 --> 00:12:55,941
[chuckles awkwardly]

268
00:12:56,484 --> 00:12:57,651
- Sure.
- Yeah?

269
00:12:57,735 --> 00:12:59,528
Oh my! Okay, okay! Thank you!

270
00:12:59,612 --> 00:13:01,655
Perfect! Thank you, thank you!

271
00:13:01,739 --> 00:13:03,782
[Tim] Alright,
I think we should all head inside.

272
00:13:03,866 --> 00:13:05,284
- Okay, let's go!
- Sure thing.

273
00:13:05,367 --> 00:13:06,911
Thank you. Seriously, thank you.

274
00:13:06,994 --> 00:13:08,996
- I'll make it up to you.
- My goodness.

275
00:13:09,079 --> 00:13:10,164
The life of a celebrity.

276
00:13:15,002 --> 00:13:16,337
[relaxing music playing over speakers]

277
00:13:16,420 --> 00:13:17,838
[Bartender] Good evening, Attorney.

278
00:13:18,339 --> 00:13:20,925
Uh, one bottle of beer, please.

279
00:13:21,550 --> 00:13:22,551
[bottle cap pops]

280
00:13:24,053 --> 00:13:25,346
Thank you.

281
00:13:28,307 --> 00:13:30,559
So, what do you have for me?

282
00:13:31,519 --> 00:13:34,522
I went to her sibling's place,
but Esther wasn't there.

283
00:13:35,147 --> 00:13:36,732
Even they don't know where she is.

284
00:13:37,233 --> 00:13:39,235
Do you think they were telling the truth?

285
00:13:39,318 --> 00:13:41,904
Esther's been avoiding
being charged with fraud.

286
00:13:41,987 --> 00:13:43,697
It's been a month.

287
00:13:44,198 --> 00:13:46,534
She could be out of the country by now.

288
00:13:46,617 --> 00:13:50,579
[relaxing music continues]

289
00:13:50,663 --> 00:13:53,457
Are you sure about any of this?

290
00:13:53,541 --> 00:13:56,168
Why reopen
something that's already closed?

291
00:13:56,919 --> 00:13:59,421
This could ruin
everything you've worked so hard for.

292
00:13:59,922 --> 00:14:02,508
I would've done this ages
ago had I not lost my nerve.

293
00:14:04,260 --> 00:14:05,928
You know, if it weren't for you,

294
00:14:06,637 --> 00:14:10,140
I would've been in prison a long time ago
for a crime I didn't commit.

295
00:14:11,225 --> 00:14:15,771
What about others like me?
Those you can still help?

296
00:14:16,939 --> 00:14:20,401
Don't all the good things you've done…

297
00:14:20,484 --> 00:14:22,903
cancel out that one bad?

298
00:14:26,323 --> 00:14:28,742
[reporter] <i>She's known as</i>
<i>the stylist to big-name celebrities</i>

299
00:14:28,826 --> 00:14:30,870
<i>like Vice Ganda and Anne Curtis.</i>

300
00:14:30,953 --> 00:14:34,415
<i>Now, Mel Montenegro has her sights</i>
<i>on something even bigger.</i>

301
00:14:34,498 --> 00:14:36,333
"MEL MONTENEGRO REVEALS
DREAM RETIREMENT HOME WITH BESTIES"

302
00:14:36,417 --> 00:14:37,751
<i>Her retirement home.</i>

303
00:14:38,127 --> 00:14:40,087
<i>Far from slowing down anytime soon,</i>

304
00:14:40,170 --> 00:14:43,048
<i>Mel, together with</i>
<i>her friends Alice and Beth,</i>

305
00:14:43,132 --> 00:14:47,094
<i>has begun renovating the house where</i>
<i>they plan to grow old and retire together.</i>

306
00:14:47,177 --> 00:14:49,763
<i>Surprisingly, their husbands</i>
<i>and kids will be moving in too.</i>

307
00:14:49,847 --> 00:14:51,932
[Alice] <i>Our kids will leave us eventually.</i>

308
00:14:52,016 --> 00:14:54,101
- [Mel] <i>Mm-hmm!</i>
- [Beth] <i>And our husbands?</i>

309
00:14:54,184 --> 00:14:55,519
<i>We could get tired of them!</i>

310
00:14:55,603 --> 00:14:57,646
[laughter]

311
00:14:57,730 --> 00:14:59,189
<i>- Right?</i>
- [Mel] <i>Come on now.</i>

312
00:14:59,273 --> 00:15:00,399
<i>Hey, kidding aside…</i>

313
00:15:00,482 --> 00:15:02,985
<i>This house will</i>
<i>serve as our vacation home.</i>

314
00:15:03,068 --> 00:15:05,779
<i>Somewhere we can meet anytime we want to.</i>

315
00:15:05,863 --> 00:15:07,907
<i>It'll be our home base.</i>

316
00:15:07,990 --> 00:15:09,408
<i>And actually,</i>

317
00:15:09,491 --> 00:15:11,785
<i>we had the option</i>
<i>to build the house from scratch,</i>

318
00:15:11,869 --> 00:15:14,496
<i>but we chose to renovate instead</i>

319
00:15:14,580 --> 00:15:16,081
<i>because we wanted to honor our friend</i>

320
00:15:16,165 --> 00:15:17,374
<i>who passed away.</i>

321
00:15:17,458 --> 00:15:19,084
[somber music playing]

322
00:15:19,168 --> 00:15:21,003
[young Mel] <i>We've</i>
<i>been waiting forever for Louisa.</i>

323
00:15:21,086 --> 00:15:23,088
<i>She's not picking up her phone.</i>

324
00:15:23,172 --> 00:15:24,757
<i>Maybe she's having</i>
<i>a hard time carrying her gift.</i>

325
00:15:24,840 --> 00:15:25,966
[sighs]

326
00:15:27,259 --> 00:15:30,554
<i>Hey! Your friend got into another fight!</i>

327
00:15:32,932 --> 00:15:36,060
<i>- Where could she be?</i>
