00:23:03,924 --> 00:23:05,926
<i>- Edong, let's go.</i>
<i>- You're one to talk!</i>

472
00:23:06,009 --> 00:23:07,219
<i>Isn't your mom a mistress?!</i>

473
00:23:08,136 --> 00:23:09,971
<i>- What about you?</i>
<i>- Beth!</i>

474
00:23:10,055 --> 00:23:13,350
<i>Your father is so vile</i>
<i>that he killed your mother!</i>

475
00:23:13,433 --> 00:23:17,062
<i>- How dare you!</i>
<i>- Ouch! Let me go!</i>

476
00:23:17,145 --> 00:23:18,188
- [Louisa grunts]
- [blow lands]

477
00:23:19,397 --> 00:23:21,233
<i>- You bastard!</i>
<i>- How dare you!</i>

478
00:23:21,316 --> 00:23:22,442
<i>Louisa!</i>

479
00:23:22,526 --> 00:23:24,069
<i>You bastard! I'll tear out your hair!</i>

480
00:23:24,152 --> 00:23:27,155
<i>You're going to regret that!</i>
<i>You're dead, you hear me?!</i>

481
00:23:27,239 --> 00:23:30,617
<i>- Screw you!</i>
<i>- I will kill you, witch!</i>

482
00:23:30,700 --> 00:23:33,453
- [Louisa] <i>Coward!</i>
<i>- Let's go, Erica!</i>

483
00:23:33,537 --> 00:23:36,873
[young Beth]
<i>We were just protecting Erica.</i>

484
00:23:36,957 --> 00:23:39,543
<i>Are you saying</i>
<i>that Louisa and Edong hit each other?</i>

485
00:23:40,252 --> 00:23:41,503
<i>Yes, sir.</i>

486
00:23:41,586 --> 00:23:45,048
<i>And that's not the only</i>
<i>time that they had a fight, is it?</i>

487
00:23:45,423 --> 00:23:47,217
<i>According to Lemuel Soria,</i>

488
00:23:47,300 --> 00:23:49,803
<i>the two also had</i>
<i>an argument at the market.</i>

489
00:23:49,886 --> 00:23:51,263
<i>And you also witnessed that.</i>

490
00:23:52,013 --> 00:23:54,724
[Louisa] <i>What are you doing?</i>
<i>Are you using drugs?</i>

491
00:23:54,808 --> 00:23:56,101
[young Edong] <i>Stay out of this!</i>

492
00:23:56,184 --> 00:23:58,436
<i>It's my business! It's my brother's money!</i>

493
00:23:58,520 --> 00:23:59,813
<i>Louisa, stop.</i>

494
00:23:59,896 --> 00:24:01,648
<i>- That's my brother's money!</i>
<i>- Edong!</i>

495
00:24:02,774 --> 00:24:05,735
[young Erica] <i>Yes. I saw it happen.</i>

496
00:24:07,904 --> 00:24:09,990
[young Lucas] <i>I knew</i>
<i>they'd pin this on my brother.</i>

497
00:24:10,866 --> 00:24:14,286
[young Erica] <i>But,</i>
<i>Lucas, Miss Esther saw him.</i>

498
00:24:14,369 --> 00:24:16,037
<i>And what he's wearing that day…</i>

499
00:24:16,121 --> 00:24:18,915
- [Louisa] <i>Jerk!</i>
<i>- I will kill you!</i>

500
00:24:18,999 --> 00:24:20,458
[grunting]

501
00:24:20,542 --> 00:24:23,795
<i>The man who killed</i>
<i>Louisa was wearing the same thing.</i>

502
00:24:23,879 --> 00:24:26,965
- [boat engine revving]
- [water lapping]

503
00:24:27,048 --> 00:24:30,218
<i>Erica, I know it's</i>
<i>easy to blame my brother.</i>

504
00:24:30,302 --> 00:24:34,306
<i>But believe me, he isn't capable of that.</i>

505
00:24:35,348 --> 00:24:39,102
<i>- You trust him that much?</i>
<i>- I know my brother.</i>

506
00:24:40,896 --> 00:24:43,440
- [young Mel] <i>Louisa!</i>
- [grunting]

507
00:24:47,110 --> 00:24:49,237
<i>Does your brother have a scar on his back?</i>

508
00:24:51,239 --> 00:24:53,033
[young Edong grunts]

509
00:24:55,827 --> 00:24:58,246
[grunting]

510
00:24:58,330 --> 00:25:02,834
<i>Sir, I didn't kill her. Please believe me.</i>

511
00:25:02,918 --> 00:25:05,212
<i>Esther Castro saw you.</i>

512
00:25:05,879 --> 00:25:10,175
<i>You were running</i>
<i>away from the crime scene.</i>

513
00:25:10,926 --> 00:25:15,055
<i>You were wearing a black hoodie and a cap.</i>

514
00:25:15,388 --> 00:25:18,183
<i>Louisa's friends also said</i>

515
00:25:18,266 --> 00:25:22,562
<i>that you threatened to kill her!</i>

516
00:25:22,646 --> 00:25:24,105
<i>- You're scum!</i>
- [thuds]

517
00:25:25,565 --> 00:25:27,567
[grunting]

518
00:25:28,360 --> 00:25:30,779
- [groaning]
<i>- Tell the truth!</i>

519
00:25:31,363 --> 00:25:34,991
<i>I didn't kill her, sir!</i>

520
00:25:36,076 --> 00:25:38,954
- [grunting, groaning]
<i>- Confess!</i>

521
00:25:39,329 --> 00:25:42,540
[morose music playing]

522
00:25:42,624 --> 00:25:45,377
[grunting]

523
00:25:46,628 --> 00:25:49,881
- [body thuds]
- [whimpers, groans]

524
00:25:54,302 --> 00:25:58,223
<i>Are you really not going to confess? Hmm?</i>

525
00:25:59,266 --> 00:26:01,101
- [blow lands]
- [grunts]

526
00:26:02,727 --> 00:26:03,770
[coughs]

527
00:26:05,522 --> 00:26:07,816
- [Celestino grunts]
- [young Edong whimpers]

528
00:26:09,025 --> 00:26:13,071
<i>I've waited so long</i>
<i>to see you behind bars, you bastard!</i>

529
00:26:13,154 --> 00:26:14,239
[grunts]

530
00:26:14,322 --> 00:26:17,701
<i>My son has been</i>
<i>in and out of rehab because of you!</i>

531
00:26:17,784 --> 00:26:19,160
[coughs, groans]

532
00:26:19,244 --> 00:26:24,124
<i>You ruined my family, you bastard!</i>

533
00:26:24,207 --> 00:26:26,459
<i>- You bastard!</i>
- [grunts]

534
00:26:28,169 --> 00:26:29,379
[grunts]

535
00:26:29,462 --> 00:26:31,381
<i>Sir, he was already doing drugs when…</i>

536
00:26:31,464 --> 00:26:32,424
[winces]

537
00:26:32,507 --> 00:26:34,134
<i>…I met him.</i>

538
00:26:34,217 --> 00:26:35,218
[Celestino]<i> You liar!</i>

539
00:26:35,302 --> 00:26:36,761
- [kick lands]
- [wails]

540
00:26:36,845 --> 00:26:39,472
- [kick lands]
- [wailing]

541
00:26:40,807 --> 00:26:42,642
<i>Please stop!</i>

542
00:26:43,184 --> 00:26:48,523
[labored breathing, grunting]

543
00:26:51,109 --> 00:26:53,903
[grunting, coughing]

544
00:26:53,987 --> 00:26:58,241
[foreboding music playing]

545
00:27:07,334 --> 00:27:09,711
<i>Please have mercy on me, sir.</i>

546
00:27:12,339 --> 00:27:14,382
- [breathes deeply, shakily]
- [foreboding music fades]

547
00:27:14,799 --> 00:27:17,635
<i>I still want to go</i>
<i>home and see my brother, sir!</i>

548
00:27:18,762 --> 00:27:20,680
<i>No one's going home.</i>

549
00:27:21,389 --> 00:27:23,266
<i>I want to go home.</i>

550
00:27:23,350 --> 00:27:25,518
<i>When I'm done with you,</i>

551
00:27:26,561 --> 00:27:29,814
<i>you'll be picked up from the garbage dump!</i>

552
00:27:30,357 --> 00:27:33,401
<i>That's where scum like you belongs!</i>

553
00:27:34,569 --> 00:27:35,779
<i>Sir…</i>

554
00:27:36,738 --> 00:27:38,073
<i>Sir.</i>

555
00:27:38,156 --> 00:27:40,158
<i>Sir, please don't hurt me.</i>

556
00:27:40,241 --> 00:27:43,161
[tense music playing]

557
00:27:43,244 --> 00:27:45,080
<i>- Take this!</i>
- [grunts, coughs]

558
00:27:47,374 --> 00:27:48,708
[sobs]

559
00:27:48,792 --> 00:27:51,961
<i>Sir, have you already</i>
<i>checked what I told you?</i>

560
00:27:52,045 --> 00:27:55,715
<i>Even if I didn't see the man's face,</i>
<i>I'm sure he has a scar on his back.</i>

561
00:27:55,799 --> 00:27:57,759
<i>It's impossible Edong killed Louisa</i>

562
00:27:57,842 --> 00:27:59,177
<i>because he doesn't have that!</i>

563
00:27:59,260 --> 00:28:01,513
<i>You're the only one</i>
<i>among you four who said that.</i>

564
00:28:01,596 --> 00:28:05,517
<i>Edong Santiago has</i>
<i>long been a danger to Amurao.</i>

565
00:28:06,142 --> 00:28:10,772
<i>We have a chance to help all of Amurao</i>

566
00:28:10,855 --> 00:28:12,899
<i>but you refuse to do it?!</i>

567
00:28:12,982 --> 00:28:15,318
<i>Do you want to go to jail?!</i>

568
00:28:15,402 --> 00:28:19,823
<i>I can have you arrested</i>
<i>for obstruction of justice!</i>

569
00:28:20,240 --> 00:28:21,616
<i>Is that what you want?!</i>

570
00:28:21,699 --> 00:28:26,246
[unsettling music playing]

571
00:28:26,329 --> 00:28:29,707
[upbeat music playing over speakers]

572
00:28:36,005 --> 00:28:39,342
[upbeat disco music playing over speakers]

573
00:28:39,426 --> 00:28:40,969
[Mel on video] <i>And actually,</i>

574
00:28:41,052 --> 00:28:43,138
<i>we had an option</i>
<i>to build the house from scratch.</i>

575
00:28:43,221 --> 00:28:45,890
<i>But we chose to renovate it instead</i>

576
00:28:45,974 --> 00:28:49,352
<i>because we wanted</i>
<i>to honor our friend who passed away.</i>

577
00:28:49,436 --> 00:28:53,356
[uneasy music playing]

578
00:28:56,234 --> 00:28:59,821
[Alice on tv]
<i>If Louisa were still alive…</i>

579
00:28:59,904 --> 00:29:01,364
[overlapping chatter]

580
00:29:01,448 --> 00:29:04,659
<i>…she'd surely be with</i>
<i>us getting this house built.</i>

581
00:29:04,743 --> 00:29:07,537
[laughter, overlapping chatter]

582
00:29:07,620 --> 00:29:10,874
[Beth on TV] <i>It's too</i>
<i>soon to build a retirement house?</i>

583
00:29:10,957 --> 00:29:13,877
<i>Well, you know how</i>
<i>unpredictable life is, right?</i>

584
00:29:13,960 --> 00:29:17,297
[inmate 1] Keep it down.
Edong's focused on the news.

585
00:29:17,380 --> 00:29:18,631
[inmates laugh]

586
00:29:18,715 --> 00:29:21,092
[inmate 2] The news? [chuckles]
Or those women?!

587
00:29:21,176 --> 00:29:24,053
[inmates cackling]

588
00:29:24,137 --> 00:29:25,263
[inmate 3] He's delusional!

589
00:29:25,346 --> 00:29:28,141
[cackling continues]

590
00:29:28,224 --> 00:29:33,354
[dramatic music playing]

591
00:29:34,731 --> 00:29:36,733
[exhales deeply]

592
00:29:38,318 --> 00:29:39,736
[exhales heavily]

593
00:29:40,653 --> 00:29:41,946
[exhales sharply]

594
00:29:43,239 --> 00:29:45,033
[zipper slides open]

595
00:29:45,116 --> 00:29:48,828
[uneasy music playing]

596
00:29:53,124 --> 00:29:54,751
[clicks]

597
00:29:54,834 --> 00:29:56,336
[clicking]

598
00:29:56,419 --> 00:29:59,798
[uneasy music continues]

599
00:30:04,385 --> 00:30:05,804
[young Beth] <i>Let's tell the police</i>

600
00:30:05,887 --> 00:30:07,680
<i>we saw Edong kill Louisa.</i>

601
00:30:07,764 --> 00:30:09,224
<i>But he didn't kill her.</i>

602
00:30:09,307 --> 00:30:11,768
<i>You're saying that just</i>
<i>because of the scar you saw?!</i>

603
00:30:13,186 --> 00:30:14,646
[young Beth] <i>What if you're wrong?!</i>

604
00:30:14,729 --> 00:30:16,189
<i>The police are right!</i>

605
00:30:16,272 --> 00:30:18,358
<i>It was too dark and chaotic!</i>

606
00:30:19,067 --> 00:30:21,694
<i>How can you be totally</i>
<i>sure about what you saw?!</i>

607
00:30:22,111 --> 00:30:23,029
<i>I'm sure.</i>

608
00:30:23,112 --> 00:30:26,115
[young Beth] <i>All</i>
<i>the evidence points to Edong!</i>

609
00:30:26,199 --> 00:30:28,409
<i>You think all that evidence is wrong?!</i>

610
00:30:28,493 --> 00:30:30,161
<i>Only what you saw is right?!</i>

611
00:30:31,037 --> 00:30:33,706
[young Alice crying shakily]

612
00:30:33,790 --> 00:30:35,667
<i>I thought you believed me.</i>

613
00:30:35,750 --> 00:30:37,001
<i>Of course, we do!</i>

614
00:30:37,085 --> 00:30:38,711
<i>We believe you, Erica.</i>

615
00:30:39,170 --> 00:30:43,258
<i>Only you believe what you saw!</i>

616
00:30:43,675 --> 00:30:45,218
<i>But you could be wrong!</i>

617
00:30:45,927 --> 00:30:48,513
<i>- Admit it!</i>
<i>- But I'm sure of it, Beth!</i>

618
00:30:48,972 --> 00:30:51,724
<i>But I'm sure Edong killed Louisa!</i>

619
00:30:53,309 --> 00:30:55,019
<i>We saw him that day.</i>

620
00:30:55,103 --> 00:30:57,522
<i>He was really angry at us and Louisa.</i>

621
00:30:58,439 --> 00:31:01,776
<i>What if he gets released</i>
<i>because we refuse to help with this case?!</i>

622
00:31:03,278 --> 00:31:04,612
<i>Can we handle that?</i>

623
00:31:06,573 --> 00:31:08,449
<i>They'll blame all of us.</i>

624
00:31:08,533 --> 00:31:10,118
<i>But we're still helping them.</i>

625
00:31:10,201 --> 00:31:11,703
<i>They just don't want to accept the truth!</i>

626
00:31:11,786 --> 00:31:14,289
<i>But I'm not convinced by your truth!</i>

627
00:31:14,372 --> 00:31:16,499
[cries, sniffles]

628
00:31:16,583 --> 00:31:18,376
<i>He killed Louisa!</i>

629
00:31:18,459 --> 00:31:20,044
[sobbing]

630
00:31:20,128 --> 00:31:22,505
[young Beth] <i>Don't</i>
<i>you want to seek justice?!</i>

631
00:31:22,589 --> 00:31:24,340
[all sobbing]

632
00:31:24,883 --> 00:31:26,759
<i>Think about it, Erica.</i>

633
00:31:28,261 --> 00:31:30,638
<i>How can you be so sure about what you saw?</i>

634
00:31:31,306 --> 00:31:32,891
<i>What if you're wrong?</i>

635
00:31:33,308 --> 00:31:35,393
<i>I can't be wrong, Beth!</i>

636
00:31:35,476 --> 00:31:38,771
<i>You should take a hard</i>
<i>look at what kind of friend you are!</i>

637
00:31:38,855 --> 00:31:41,316
- [Mel sobbing]
<i>- Maybe they're right!</i>

638
00:31:42,525 --> 00:31:45,653
<i>You can't admit you could</i>
<i>be wrong because of Lucas!</i>

639
00:31:46,487 --> 00:31:49,365
<i>You're selfish, Erica! You're so selfish!</i>

640
00:31:49,449 --> 00:31:51,659
[all sobbing]

641
00:31:51,743 --> 00:31:52,994
<i>Beth!</i>

642
00:31:53,077 --> 00:31:55,413
[uneasy music continues]

643
00:31:55,496 --> 00:31:56,539
[Celestino] <i>Search everywhere!</i>

644
00:31:57,081 --> 00:31:58,374
[metal clanks]

645
00:31:58,458 --> 00:31:59,834
<i>What are you doing?</i>

646
00:31:59,918 --> 00:32:02,337
<i>We have a warrant to search your house!</i>

647
00:32:02,420 --> 00:32:04,172
[objects clattering]

648
00:32:04,255 --> 00:32:06,132
[policeman] <i>Sir, come here!</i>

649
00:32:06,215 --> 00:32:08,009
[tense music playing]

650
00:32:08,092 --> 00:32:09,886
- [watch rattles]
- [policeman sighs]

651
00:32:11,846 --> 00:32:12,931
[Celestino chuckles]

652
00:32:13,848 --> 00:32:17,352
<i>We found where</i>
<i>Edong kept the stolen items.</i>

653
00:32:18,144 --> 00:32:19,979
<i>According to your statements,</i>

654
00:32:20,480 --> 00:32:23,483
<i>Louisa's watch was missing.</i>

655
00:32:26,986 --> 00:32:28,446
<i>Excuse me.</i>

656
00:32:28,529 --> 00:32:32,575
[Celestino] <i>I want</i>
<i>you to tell us if that's Louisa's watch.</i>

657
00:32:32,659 --> 00:32:36,996
[tense music playing]

658
00:32:56,474 --> 00:32:57,684
<i>Yes.</i>

659
00:32:59,894 --> 00:33:01,562
<i>This is Louisa's watch.</i>

660
00:33:01,646 --> 00:33:05,233
[tense music continues]

661
00:33:15,994 --> 00:33:17,870
[crying shakily]

662
00:33:20,331 --> 00:33:22,125
<i>It's Louisa's watch.</i>

663
00:33:22,208 --> 00:33:24,919
[tense music continues]

664
00:33:25,920 --> 00:33:27,046
<i>Yes.</i>

665
00:33:28,840 --> 00:33:30,341
<i>That's her watch.</i>

666
00:33:31,134 --> 00:33:35,138
- [crying softly]
- [uneasy music continues]

667
00:33:37,974 --> 00:33:39,058
<i>But--</i>

668
00:33:39,142 --> 00:33:43,312
[tense music continues]

669
00:33:45,356 --> 00:33:46,899
<i>I'm sorry.</i> [sniffles]

670
00:33:46,983 --> 00:33:51,529
[music intensifies]

671
00:33:51,612 --> 00:33:54,365
<i>This is complete nonsense!</i>
<i>I didn't kill anyone!</i>

672
00:33:55,324 --> 00:33:57,160
<i>Lucas! Lucas!</i>

673
00:33:57,243 --> 00:33:58,870
<i>Bro, I didn't kill anyone!</i>

674
00:33:58,953 --> 00:34:01,414
<i>Please believe me, bro! I'm innocent!</i>

675
00:34:01,998 --> 00:34:03,916
<i>Bro, I didn't kill anyone!</i>

676
00:34:04,375 --> 00:34:06,210
<i>- Bro!</i>
<i>- Lock him up!</i>

677
00:34:06,294 --> 00:34:08,212
<i>You all did this to me!</i>

678
00:34:09,130 --> 00:34:10,715
<i>Bro!</i>

679
00:34:10,798 --> 00:34:14,218
[morose music playing]

680
00:34:22,185 --> 00:34:27,690
[telephone ringing]

681
00:34:30,068 --> 00:34:31,944
[ringing continues]

682
00:34:33,780 --> 00:34:35,031
[ringing]

683
00:34:38,659 --> 00:34:41,120
[Edong] <i>I saw your friends on TV.</i>

684
00:34:41,704 --> 00:34:43,706
<i>They looked so happy.</i>

685
00:34:44,540 --> 00:34:47,251
<i>It seemed like they had no conscience.</i>

686
00:34:47,794 --> 00:34:49,003
Who's this?

687
00:34:50,004 --> 00:34:51,631
[Edong] <i>Attorney…</i>

688
00:34:52,090 --> 00:34:54,092
Have you forgotten me?

689
00:34:55,301 --> 00:34:56,969
This is Edong,

690
00:34:57,512 --> 00:34:59,722
the first person you put in jail.

691
00:35:00,223 --> 00:35:04,602
<i>And you're not</i>
<i>supposed to forget your first.</i>

692
00:35:04,685 --> 00:35:07,772
[dramatic music playing]

693
00:35:07,855 --> 00:35:09,816
How did you get my number?

694
00:35:12,568 --> 00:35:14,112
[Edong sighs]

695
00:35:14,195 --> 00:35:16,989
